  "prompt": "How many grafts are needed to get a full beard by facial hair transplant? How much will it cost in India?",
  "response": "The number of grafts needed for a full beard transplant depends on several factors, including the current density of your beard, the desired density, and the size of the area to be covered. On average:\n\n- **500 to 1,500 grafts** are typically needed for a light or patchy beard enhancement.\n- **1,500 to 3,000 grafts** are usually required for a full beard transplant.\n- **3,000 to 5,000 grafts** may be needed for those with very little facial hair or for a denser, fuller beard.\n\n### Cost of Beard Transplant in India\nThe cost of a beard transplant in India varies depending on the clinic, the surgeon's experience, the city, and the number of grafts required. On average:\n\n- **Cost per graft**: \u20b930 to \u20b9150 (approx. $0.40 to $2 USD per graft)\n- **Total cost**: \u20b950,000 to \u20b93,00,000 (approx. $670 to $4,000 USD) for a full beard transplant.\n\n### Factors Affecting Cost:\n1. **Number of grafts**: More grafts mean higher costs.\n2. **Clinic reputation**: Premium clinics or experienced surgeons may charge more.\n3. **Location**: Costs may vary between metropolitan cities and smaller towns.\n4. **Technique used**: FUE (Follicular Unit Extraction) is more expensive than FUT (Follicular Unit Transplantation).\n\nIt\u2019s advisable to consult with a qualified surgeon to determine the exact number of grafts needed and to get a personalized cost estimate.",
